en Germans in Czechoslovakia resisting regime:\n\nSome of the Sudeten Germans who were\nmoved into the interior of Czechoslovakia\nin 1945 \"are even refusing to register for\nmilitary service,\"\nThey are also demanding the right to return\nto their former homes in connection with the government's operation\n\"for founding settlements in the border territory.\"\n\nComment: This is the first reliable report\nof overt resistance to the regime by elements of the German minority.\nEfforts to placate the Sudetens, including the restitution of Czechoslovak\ncitizenship last April, have apparently met with little success.\n\nThe Sudeten Germans have been particularly\nanxious to return to their homeland since Premier Siroky announced in\nSeptember that the government would take special steps to revive the\neconomy of the border areas.\n\nLATIN AMERICA\n\n7.\n\n- 6", "token_count": 132, "token_end_0based": 131, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "eastern europe 6 sudeten germans in czechoslovakia resisting regime some of the sudeten germans who were moved into the interior of czechoslovakia in 1945 are even refusing to register for military service they are also demanding the right to return to their former homes in connection with the government's operation for founding settlements in the border territory comment this is the first reliable report of overt resistance to the regime by elements of the german minority efforts to placate the sudetens including the restitution of czechoslovak citizenship last april have apparently met with little success the sudeten germans have been particularly anxious to return to their homeland since premier siroky announced in september that the government would take special steps to revive the economy of the border areas latin america 7 6", "unred_source_page": 6}
